{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a2301fbc-1d51-4a14-baaa-0aa03300c4fc","content":"Empty directory — no existing files to integrate with. Here's the full configuration:\n\n## Environment Variables\n\nSet these on your container for NativeAOT crash dump collection:\n\n| Variable | Value | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` | `1` | Enables automatic dump on crash |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` | `4` | Full memory dump (use `2` for heap-only) |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` | `/tmp/dumps/core.%p.%t` | Dump path (`%p`=PID, `%t`=timestamp) |\n| `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` | `/opt/tools/createdump` | Custom createdump location |\n| `DOTNET_EnableCrashReport` | `1` | JSON crash report alongside dump |\n\n## Pod Spec Changes\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: my-app\n      # ... your existing image/command ...\n      env:\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/tmp/dumps/core.%p.%t\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n        - name: DOTNET_EnableCrashReport\n          value: \"1\"\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add:\n            - SYS_PTRACE          # required by createdump\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi           # adjust based on app memory footprint\n```\n\n### Key notes\n\n- **`SYS_PTRACE`** is required — `createdump` uses `ptrace` to read process memory.\n- **`emptyDir`** keeps dumps on the node until the pod is deleted. Swap to a **PersistentVolumeClaim** if you need dumps to survive pod restarts.\n- **Dump type `4`** (full) can be large. Use `2` (heap) or `3` (triage) to reduce size.\n- **`DOTNET_EnableCrashReport=1`** writes a companion `.json` file with stack traces and exception info — very useful for NativeAOT since symbols may be stripped.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0bee3f48-75de-4f65-abc0-4cae4830167f","outputTokens":638,"requestId":"980C:18FEB2:5943C5B:61C6B2E:69F406C2"},"id":"22cd31b2-b074-4901-8d77-8b995b7b90b3","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:50:06.652Z","parentId":"9ad43831-8fc0-490b-acf3-1868282c2ca3"}
